node.text:
No one ever sees the iceberg that exists UNDER the water. The countless mistakes and awkward moments before we broadcast our lives and relationships on social media. The times we weren’t on the same page or when I was ignoring all her signs and taking on my self assigned role as the white knight by publicly claiming “my woman” via grand gesture after grand gesture. 

I feel like our culture needs to see more examples of happy marriages who have done and are doing the work (it never stops) who have made it through messy and uncomfortable times along the way. To me #goals are about imperfection and talking about the work of relationships. Showing the humanity not just the highlight reel.

The truth is, there is no such thing as a honeymoon phase: i believe it’s just a delay of the real, deep, messy, uncomfortable and confronting work of being in a relationship. Of course you can have amazing chemistry off the bat but I don’t think true lasting happiness can start until both parties are radically honest with what the other needs and wants. Work that most of us are too afraid to do for fear of either scaring away the person we are with or being scared away by them not being the perfect “idea” of who we want them to be or who society has told us they should be.

We all have stuff. We all have shit. Let’s stop pretending we don’t and embrace it. When we allow it in and stop rejecting it, that shit it becomes the fertilizer for the soil of unconditional love.

@emilybaldoni @wearemanenough

The love for this episode has been nothing short of overwhelming for me and my dad. Having this conversation wasn’t easy but hearing from so many of you about how healing this was to listen to means the world to us. This sums up so much of this journey for me. Emotion and vulnerability meeting. Creating a safe place that allows us to expose and express our weaknesses, our mistakes; creating a closeness that allows us to embrace our humanness…together.

It’s what I hope my kids and I can always share.

It’s what I’m starting to share with my own parents, and what I’m so thankful I could share with my dad, @sambaldoni, in this episode. 

#ManEnough #TheManEnoughPodcast

This was one of the most healing moments for my dad @sambaldoni and I. 

Thank you all for your love support, compassion and for taking the time to listen to this conversation on this episode of the @wearemanenough podcast. We were both really nervous to talk, and cry like this in public but your response has warmed our hearts and affirmed the reason why we did this.

Here’s to healing. Here’s to being enough.

#ManEnough #Undefined

This was one of the most healing moments for my dad (@sambaldoni )and I. Thank you all for your love support, compassion and for taking the time to listen to this conversation on this episode of the @wearemanenough podcast. We were both really nervous to talk, and cry like this in public but your response has warmed our hearts and affirmed the reason why we did this. 
Here’s to healing. Here’s to being enough.

node.text: Want to audition for the next film I’m producing?! @WayfarerStudios is launching a #CastingCall 🎬 Tag a friend who should audition! node.text:
Super grateful to have my friend @jayshetty sharing his wisdom and truth on The #ManEnoughPodcast this week!

Jay is a very special soul. I don’t meet many people (especially in the self-help space) who truly live what they teach. He is everything you would think he would be and more. What I appreciate so much about Jay is that he isn’t a teacher, he’s a student. He just shares what he has learned along the way and what he is learning.

Jay is incredible at making ancient wisdom accessible to the masses and he invites us and challenges us to see that service is at the core of who we are as people, and that being of service to one another—to humanity—is the only way we will ever more forward and be truly successful as a society.

Tune in to this week’s episode for such an important, urgent, and timely reminder with all the heartache going on in the world.

What can you do today to be of service to someone else?

#ManEnough

node.text:
No one ever sees the iceberg that exists UNDER the water. The countless mistakes and awkward moments before we broadcast our lives and relationships on social media. The times we weren’t on the same page or when I was ignoring all her signs and taking on my self assigned role as the white knight by publicly claiming “my woman” via grand gesture after grand gesture. 

I feel like our culture needs to see more examples of happy marriages who have done and are doing the work (it never stops) who have made it through messy and uncomfortable times along the way. To me #goals are about imperfection and talking about the work of relationships. Showing the humanity not just the highlight reel.

The truth is, there is no such thing as a honeymoon phase: i believe it’s just a delay of the real, deep, messy, uncomfortable and confronting work of being in a relationship. Of course you can have amazing chemistry off the bat but I don’t think true lasting happiness can start until both parties are radically honest with what the other needs and wants. Work that most of us are too afraid to do for fear of either scaring away the person we are with or being scared away by them not being the perfect “idea” of who we want them to be or who society has told us they should be.

We all have stuff. We all have shit. Let’s stop pretending we don’t and embrace it. When we allow it in and stop rejecting it, that shit it becomes the fertilizer for the soil of unconditional love.

@emilybaldoni @wearemanenough

The love for this episode has been nothing short of overwhelming for me and my dad. Having this conversation wasn’t easy but hearing from so many of you about how healing this was to listen to means the world to us. This sums up so much of this journey for me. Emotion and vulnerability meeting. Creating a safe place that allows us to expose and express our weaknesses, our mistakes; creating a closeness that allows us to embrace our humanness…together.

It’s what I hope my kids and I can always share.

It’s what I’m starting to share with my own parents, and what I’m so thankful I could share with my dad, @sambaldoni, in this episode. 

#ManEnough #TheManEnoughPodcast

node.text:
You may be wondering what the heck is happening in these pictures? 

Honestly… it’s hard to explain. But all I can say is that @emilybaldoni and I are eternally grateful for the heart opening, love explosion that happened over the last four days with our friend/brother/healer @drjohnamaral and his powerhouse healer/wife @christinaamaral .

All the love and fear that we experience on a daily basis lives inside of us. We so rarely allow ourselves to express all that we feel and often times end up suppressing it, burying it and never letting it out. We also do the same thing with love and joy. We don’t allow ourselves to feel it.

Unexpressed pain and fear live in our bodies and affect every aspect of our life and often times lead to so many illnesses (both mental and physical). 

But the good news is that healing is possible. Allowing ourselves to express these feelings is a radical act of love, for both ourselves and the world around us. And allowing ourselves, especially us men to feel our feelings, to express our pain through movement and sound, and to be vulnerable in front of the people we love and our partners is, I believe, the future of not just healing but our collective liberation. A love liberation. 

I’ve been trying to take off the armor that’s protecting my heart for years. Trying to break free and experience what true freedom feels like in my body and spirit feels like. And while I am far from having arrived, I’ve seen and felt glimpses of what that freedom feels like.

And none of this would be possible without my helpmate, my lover, my wife starting this journey herself and inspiring me to dive in. 

 I love the shit out of you sweetheart. 

Here’s to feeling. Here’s to healing. Here’s to freedom.

When I first got to sit down and talk with @comedianlilrel on the set of #Clouds, I was so moved by how open and real he was, and I am so damn grateful that he said yes to coming on The #ManEnoughPodcast. 

This man is talented, HILARIOUS, honest, and just an all-around special dude. 

Tune in to hear him talk about grief, masculinity in the Black community, fatherhood, and body image, as well as successfully convincing me I should be getting pedicures. 😉

Lil Rel Howery: Strength in Imperfection
Available Monday, 8/9
Follow manenough.com/podcast to listen (link in bio)

#ManEnough #Undefined
